premise_source_doc_sentence: Thus , due to this emphasis on prayer in the early church , lengthy passages of the New Testament are prayers or canticles  (  see also the Book of Odes  )  , such as the Prayer for forgiveness , the Lord 's Prayer , the Magnificat , the Benedictus , Jesus ' prayer to the one true God , Praise be to the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ , the Believers ' Prayer , may this cup be taken from me , Pray that you will not fall into temptation , Saint Stephen 's Prayer , Simon Magus ' Prayer , pray that we may be delivered from wicked and evil men , Maranatha .
The most common prayer among Christians is the `` Lord 's Prayer '' , which according to the gospel accounts  (  e.g. Matthew 6:9 -13  )  is how Jesus taught his disciples to pray .
The Lord 's Prayer is a central prayer in Christianity .
`` The Lord 's Prayer '' is a model for prayers of adoration , confession and petition in Christianity .
